review_blob: Bottle 750ml, pours hazy yellow with thin white head. Aroma of citrus and wheat.  Light flavor of wheat, citrus, and lemons, but overall a bit weak.  Still a very refreshing beer for any occasion.

Bottle, pours amber with beige head.  Aroma of hops and caramel malts.  Taste is malts, caramel, and slightly bitter hoppy finish.  I think this is a decent beer, and if it were a "craft beer" it would be rated higher.
Bottle, pours cloudy gold with medium white head.  Aroma of yeast, wheat, and some citrus.  Taste of citrus and wheat and high carbonation.  A refreshing beer that everyone likes, even the girls.

Bottle, pours black with tan head.  Aroma of chocolate malts, coffee, and some hops.  Big flavor of chocolate and roast coffee, balanced with some sweetness.  Warming alcohol finish,  this is a great imperial stout.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bottle, pours dark amber with brown head.  Aroma of dark fruits, caramel, yeast.  Smooth taste of dark fruits with good complexity and some alcohol on the finish.  A great beer you can find in most quality beer stores, I always have a few in the fridge.

750ml Bottle, pours dark brown with thin beige head.  Aroma of dark fruits, caramel, sugars.  Flavor of dark fruits, caramel, chocolate, and sweetness throughout.  Mouthfeel is great with medium body and moderate carbonation.  Obviously not as complex as some other Belgian-style strong ales but I really enjoy what this one offers.  $7 a bottle is great for me too.

beer_brewer_name: Krebs Brewing Company / Petes Place / Choc Beer
review_blob: Bottle, pours orange with small white head.  Aroma of some citrus hops and light malts.  Taste is slightly sweet with light hops and balanced malts.  Medium body and slightly bitter finish.   Ok beer.
beer_name: Petes Place Basement Batch Pale Ale

review_blob: Bottle, pours black with mocha head.  Aroma of chocolate, coffee, oak, hops, and malts.  Really rich, sweet flavor of chocolate, coffee and malts with an interesting oak finish.  Really reminds me of the Rasputin XII I had last week.  This is a fantastic beer and reasonably priced too.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged

review_blob: Bottle, pours dark brown with thin tan head.  Aroma is sweet with dark fruits, caramel and malts.  Great appearance and aroma.  Big flavor of dark fruits, caramel, chocolate, coffee, and dark malts.  Really impressive beer with full body and warm finish.
beer_name: Gouden Carolus Cuvee Van De Keizer Blauw/Blue

beer_brewer_name: Krebs Brewing Company / Petes Place / Choc Beer
review_blob: Bottle, pours black with tan head.  Aroma of dark malts with some chocolate and coffee.  Flavors of roasted malts, chocolate and some hops.  Well balanced, medium body with some sweetness and nice finish.  This was a surprisingly good beer.

Bottle, pours gold with white head.  Aroma of light hops and some citrus.  Taste is light hops and malts and some spice on the finish.  Not bad at all, very drinkable.  Not a typical IPA though if youre a hophead.

Bottle, pours dark red with a big tan head.  Aroma of massive hops and a lot of malts.  Taste is immediate powerful hops with some malts and fruits.  Very aggressive beer not for the feint of heart.  Enjoyable but be ready for it.

Bottle, pours a light brown with small head.  Aroma of spices, hops and some light fruit.  Taste was sweet, fruity, spicy, and light hops.  Medium body made it very drinkable.  Not as good as other tripels but still a good beer.

Bottle, pours an orange/amber with white head.  Huge aroma of hops.  Taste is very hoppy at first, but has some malty sweetness to it and a nice complexity.  Hops and alcohol on the finish.  A great full bodied beer that packs a ton of flavor.  Im blaming my hangover on this beer.

Bottle, pours brown with a cream head.  Aroma of dark fruits and malts.  Complex flavor or dark fruits and caramel.  Delicious smooth mouthfeel and this beer hides the alcohol well.  These are easy to find and always great.

Bottle, pours dark brown with thin head.  Aroma of fruits, caramel, and alcohol.  Sweet flavor of malts, cherry, caramel, and dark fruits.  Alcohol on the finish, this is a strong beer.  Very enjoyable but not as complex as other quads.

Bottle, pours amber/brown with beige head.  Smells sweet, with malts and citrus.  Taste is great, very complex caramel, fruits, citrus, and a hoppy finish.  Love the full body of this beer, and it warms you from the inside out.  Ill be picking this one up whenever I can find it.
beer_name: Cigar City Warmer Winter Winter Warmer

review_blob: Bottle, pours copper with white head.  Aroma is floral with light malts.  Tastes sweet with a good amount of hops behind it.  Medium body and very drinkable, a great 6 pack to pick up if you only have access to a gas station or grocery store.
Bottle, pours copper with beige head.  Aroma of light hops and malts.  Tastes of caramel malts and light hop finish.  Decent beer, at least its 6.8% abv
Pours copper with cream head.  Aroma of smoke and honey.  Smokey flavor with malts, bacon, and caramel.  I thought it was a little thin but the rest of the group enjoyed it.

Pours brown/amber with beige foam, aroma of fruits and candy sugar.  Complex flavor of dark fruits, yeast, caramel, and sugars.  Love the mouthfeel of medium body and high carbonation.  So drinkable, this is a personal favorite.

Pours black with tan head.  Wonderful aroma of coffee, chocolate, and caramel.   Strong dark chocolate, coffee, and caramel flavor with a lingering bourbon finish.  This is a unique beer, and an improvement on the already delicious Rasputin.  Thanks to the ladyfriend for picking this one up.

Bottle pours a dark amber color with light head.  Lots of sediment in the bottom of my glass, shouldnt have let the bottle tip over on the drive over.  Strong complex aroma of fruit and caramel.  Taste is a little sweet with tons of fruits and complexity.  Medium to full body with creamy mouthfeel.  This is an elite beer, one of my favorites.

Bottle, pours a dark black with tan head.  Aroma of dark chocolate and roast, smells great.  Taste a lot of chocolate with some malt and coffee notes and a slightly bitter finish.  Good carbonation and mouthfeel.  Not as complex as other stouts, but this is just plain tasty.
Bottle, pours a light amber color with white head.  Aroma of some malt and hops, taste was the same.  Light mouthfeel, very drinkable.  Was a good starter beer for the night.
